Message.MsgText: CWXDG_I_WSGRID_InitComplete=CWXDG7001I: Job scheduler message listener interface initialization complete.
Message.Explanation: Indicates normal completion of Job scheduler message listener interface initialization.
Indicates Job scheduler received indicated exception. Job scheduler listener interface is disabled.

Message.MsgText: CWXDG_E_WSGRID_Submission_Exception=CWXDG7257E: Job submission failed due to exception {0}.
Message.Explanation: Indicates job submission request to Job Scheduler listener interface (e.g. via WSGrid command) failed due to indicated exception.

Message.MsgText: CWXDG_I_WSGRID_Listening=CWXDG7002I: Job scheduler listening on {0} queue {1}.
Message.Explanation: Indicates normal listener initialization on indicated message queue.

Message.MsgText: CWXDG_E_WSGRID_Submission_Error=CWXDG7252E: Failure to submit job {0} from {1} due to error {2}.
Message.Explanation: Indicates Job scheduler listener interface failed to submit indicated job from either repository or file due to indicated error.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure correct job source information is specified.

Message.MsgText: CWXDG_E_WSGRID_Syntax_Error=CWXDG7255E: Job submission rejected because of syntax error on keyword {0}.
Message.Explanation: Indicates job submission request to Job Scheduler listener interface (e.g. via WSGrid command) was rejected because of syntax error on indicated keyword.

Message.MsgText: CWXDG_E_WSGRID_Submission_Missing_Keyword=CWXDG7253E: Job submission rejected because required keyword {0} was not specified.
Message.Explanation: Indicates job submission request to Job Scheduler listener interface (e.g. via WSGrid command) was rejected because indicated required keyword was not specified.

Message.MsgText: CWXDG_I_WSGRID_Listener_Unavailable=CWXDG7003I: Job scheduler not listening on {0} queue {1} because queue is not defined.
Message.Explanation: Indicates Job scheduler is not listening on the indicated queue because it is not defined.

Message.MsgText: CWXDG_I_WSGRID_Submitted=CWXDG7251I: Job scheduler listener interface submitted job {0}.
Message.Explanation: Indicates Job scheduler listener interface submitted indicated job.

Message.MsgText: CWXDG_W_WSGRID_Outbound_Queue_Unavailable=CWXDG7005W: Job scheduler unable to send outbound messages on {0} queue {1} because queue is not defined.
Message.Explanation: Indicates Job scheduler is unable to send outbound messages on indicated queue due to the indicated initialization error.

Message.MsgText: CWXDG_W_WSGRID_Outbound_Queue_Broken=CWXDG7006W: Job scheduler unable to send outbound messages on {0} queue {1} due to initialization error {2}.
Message.Explanation: Indicates Job scheduler is unable to send outbound messages on indicated queue due to the indicated initialization error.

Message.MsgText: CWXDG_W_WSGRID_Not_Listening=CWXDG7004W: Job scheduler not listening on {0} queue {1} due to initialization error {2}.
Message.Explanation: Indicates Job scheduler is not listening on the indicated queue due to the indicated initialization error.
Indicates Job scheduler received indicated exception. Job scheduler listener interface can continue normal operation.

Message.MsgText: CWXDG_W_WSGRID_Unrecognized_Keyword=CWXDG7256E: Job submission proceeding with unrecognized keyword {0} ignored.
Message.Explanation: Indicates job submission request to Job Scheduler listener interface (e.g. via WSGrid command) encountered an unrecognized keyword. The keyword is ignored. The job submission continues.

Message.MsgText: CWXDG_E_WSGRID_Outbound_Queue_Broken=CWXDG7007E: Job scheduler unable to send outbound messages on {0} queue {1} due to runtime error {2}.
Message.Explanation: Indicates Job scheduler is unable to send outbound messages on indicated queue due to the indicated runtime error.

Message.MsgText: CWXDG_E_WSGRID_Submission_Mutually_Exclusive=CWXDG7254E: Job submission rejected because required mutually exclusive keywords {0} and {1} are specified.
Message.Explanation: Indicates job submission request to Job Scheduler listener interface (e.g. via WSGrid command) was rejected because indicated mutually exclusive keywords were specified.
